One of them is that they must have been a member of the party for at least two years before elections.Dr Zani also said the party remains committed to working with Jubilee on matters of BBI since it is aimed at uniting Kenyans. Aspirants planning to contest for political seats on the Orange Democratic Movement (ODM) party in 2022 elections would have to meet stringent conditions to get the ticket. 

One of them is that they must have been a member of the party for at least two years before elections. 

The Saturday Nation has reliably learnt that the National Executive Committee (NEC) in a meeting held yesterday in Nairobi adopted the recommendation from the party’s legal committee. 



