In the meeting, Mr Odinga told the leaders to go to the ground and conduct civil education on the benefits of the BBI. In particular, Mr Odinga told his troops to explain to the people the import of increasing allocation to counties by 35 percent and how each county is set to get an increment in the shareable revenue. 

Dr Zani also said the party remains committed to working with Jubilee on matters of BBI since it is aimed at uniting Kenyans. 

“To achieve this, we have resolved to work with the ruling Jubilee party and other like-minded political parties to walk this journey together to the end,” Dr Zani said. Process may be infiltrated by rivals, losing candidates may bolt out, but a successful poll may also pay dividends. Orange party will consider aspirants’ education qualifications in 2022. Jubilee was meant to signpost a renaissance for the nation. Uhuru tells DP Ruto he can’t continue eating his cake and having it too. Qualifications agency says a third of all the certificates they verify are falsified, outright fake or fraudulent.